values: tonight is our last day in nicaragua.it's kind of sad,really.i'm going to miss all 24 people in this house sooo much.this has been one of the most memorable experiences of my life.i adore this house and the children and people ive been able to meet.well im gonna go now cause i have to do other stuff.

so it's 7:30 am over here in nicaragua and i have just turned 16.one might think that their 16th birthday was important,sort of a designated time in her life when dating is "ok" in the family.truth is i feel nothing.i actually woke up and forgot it was my birthday.i hugged my mom and she's like happy birthday hunny,and im all like oh yeah.the house we`re at here is awesome.it's 3 stories high and is very colorful.you can even see a volcanoe out of the window in the living room.on this misson trip we`ve been helping in the orphanage and school so far, and my mom is even thinking about adopting 4 siblings.its amazing, they are all gorgeous and sweet.their names are marleenie,she`s 7,walter,he`s 6,kareen,she`s 4 and she was raped when she was 3 by her father and that`s why shes at the orphanage,and last genisis the baby,shes almost 2.getting them will probably be hard but im up for the challenge.i thyink im going to go now,so read this and think of me being thousands of miles away.lol

the perks of being the best friend

the perks of being the best friend are usually great nothingness, staying up till 3 am painting sporks that will later crack and break. finding the spork after months of not seeing it brings back the memories of laughing and being an add toaster oven. its things like that that make you feel better in a disagreement. like one persons being pissy, and offends you so your pissy back, but them you remember the spork painting, or the late  night kung-fu, or the rednecks down the street riding their lawnmowers, or the same rednecks putting on small banjo shows on their backporch, making fun of them was great. turning out the lights when getting ready for bed, but actually just returning from the sleepy state and talking for an hour about meaningless stuff is usually one of my favorites. being the best friend is way more than what it seems. there are no words that i can think of more than pure love. if i can find a longer word for it id like to know. but for now best friend = love and thats all im going to say about that <3.


" i loved it all, i loved the girl, i loved my friend"
